            <div type="edition" xml:space="preserve"><head>Text</head><ab><lb n="1"/>
                Sc<expan><ex>h</ex><abbr>ola</abbr></expan> coll<supplied reason="lost" cert="low">egii cent(onariorum)</supplied> <lb n="2"/>empta ex pecun<supplied reason="lost">ia quam vi</supplied><lb break="no" n="3"/>vos <note>sic</note> dederat <expan><abbr>Q</abbr><ex>uintus</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>Ulp</abbr><ex>ius</ex></expan> F<supplied reason="lost" cert="low">elix? p(raefectus)? ce</supplied><lb break="no" n="4"/><expan><abbr>nt</abbr><ex cert="low">onariorum</ex></expan> pater ad rosalia a<supplied reason="lost">nnua<certainty locus="name" match="preceding-sibling::text()" cert="low"/> <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/></supplied> <lb n="5"/>itemque ad sepulc<supplied reason="lost">r</supplied><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> <lb n="6"/>a solo inpendio <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> <lb n="7"/>et collegio <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> <lb n="8"/><del rend="erasure"><supplied reason="lost"><expan><abbr>Imp</abbr><ex>eratore</ex></expan> Antonin</supplied>o <supplied reason="lost">Au</supplied><expan><abbr>g</abbr><ex>usto</ex></expan> [III et</del>] <lb n="9"/>Com<expan><ex>a</ex><abbr>zonte</abbr></expan> co<expan><ex>n</ex><abbr>s</abbr><ex>ulibus</ex></expan>
            </ab></div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Zwei aneinanderpassende Fragmente einer Tafel. Im linken unteren Teil eine Ader im Stein schräg von links nach rechts unten verlaufend, dieser Teil des Inschriftfeldes wurde frei gelassen. Z. 3: DE-; LP-Ligatur; Z. 4: NT-, TE-, AL-Ligatur; I klein über der Querhaste des L stehend. Quintus Ulpius Felix ist auch in den Inschriften http://edh-www.adw.uni-heidelberg.de/edh/inschrift/HD020121 und http://edh-www.adw.uni-heidelberg.de/edh/inschrift/HD038313 bekannt, dort als Augustalis.</p>
            </div>
